HEADWORD: nonhereditary
<hw>nonhereditary</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>Not inheritable through
genetic transmission. Opposite of <ant>inheritable</ant>, and
<ant>heritable</ant>.</def> [Narrower terms: <stype>acquired,
nurtural</stype>; <stype>congenital, inborn, innate </stype>]⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> nontransmissible, nonheritable,
noninheritable.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

